<br />

<br />
ummmm no...  Mage fire pets are the only ones that truly cast spells. Your pets lifetap is a spell, but not one that requires mana.  If you have the leadership aa you will see your pet cast this spell, Lifetap strike. <a href="http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=1965&amp;source=Live" target="_blank">http://lucy.allakhazam.com/spell.html?id=1965&amp;source=Live</a>
<br />

<br />
You will notice that the mana cost is zero. DO NOT EVER TWITCH YOUR PET, well unless you just want to piss off a stupid cleric. Pet lifetaps are random procs, not something that your pet chain-casts until it runs out of mana.
<br />

<br />
Also, you should never rely on your pet lifetap to keep it alive, basically it's a nice perk but not something all that wonderful.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v173/ducksgoquak/Everquest/armania.jpg" border="0" />
