			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Zrae wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Ok, it's a proc - is this a proc that is affected by your pet's dex?  In other words would a shammy dex buff increase the chances of pets lifetap?  And is there a % or set number of hitpoints healed / damage done with each proc?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This is a proc that does so little damage and heals for so little it really wouldn't make much of a difference even if dex had a large effect on it. Higher dex will improve your pet dps, I would expect it wouldn't increase the chance to proc it's lifetap. From mage testing I've heard that stat equipment/buffs all affect pets, with the exception of stamina raising your pets hp, in the same way as they affect NPC's. Dex improves weapon procs, but the lifetap our pets use is innate and not tied to the weapons they're using.
<br />

<br />
The amount of hp damage done/healed is related to the level of the pet. The higher the pets level, the more damage it does. The damage done by a level 44 pet should be around 25 damage.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=490383" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kelter Skelter
<br />
da neckRomancer</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
